<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="604" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/9–2951: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The United States</hi> (<gloss target="#t_GATT1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">GATT</hi></gloss>) <hi rend="italic">Delegation to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-29">September 29,
                                1951</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <gloss target="#t_Tagg1">Tagg</gloss> 49. Fol delivered Exec Sec 10:40
                            a. m., Geneva time, Sept 29:</p>
                        <p>“My dear Mr. Executive Secretary: This is to inform you that the
                            Government of the US invokes its right under the second paragraph of the
                            operative part of the declaration by the <gloss target="#t_CP1">CP</gloss>s of September 27, 1951, and hereby suspends, effective
                            immediately and until further notice, the obligations of the US with
                            respect to Czechoslovakia under the <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>.</p>
                        <p>“Sincerely yours, Willard L. Thorp, Chairman, <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> Sixth Session of <gloss target="#t_CP1">CP</gloss>s
                            to the <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>”.</p>
                        <p>Anticipate circulation of <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss> doc in
                            Geneva and release to press in Washington.</p>
                        <p>Pls advise date publicity and text any covering release.</p>
                    </div>
